{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
[[Image:Quashnet River (Massachusetts) map.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Waquoit Bay and environs]]

'''Waquoit Bay''' is a small landlocked tidal bay on the south shore of Cape Cod in the [[United States of America|US state]] of [[Massachusetts]].  The bay is connected with [[Nantucket Sound]] and separates the towns of [[Mashpee, Massachusetts|Mashpee]] and [[Falmouth, Massachusetts|Falmouth]]. 

In the early 1960s Norwegian researcher Johannes Kr. Torn<U+00F6>e suggested the shallow bay could be the location of [[Leifsbudir]], (''Leif's booths'' or ''houses'') the long sought site of the [[Norsemen|Norse]] colony of [[Vinland]].

